<i>noun</i>: 절반 [절반], 반쪽 [반ː쪽], 반 [반ː] <i>verb</i>: 반분하다 [반ː분하다] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>절반 [절반]</dt><br>
<dd>half</dd><br>
<dd>하나를 반으로 나눔. 또는 그렇게 나눈 반.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of dividing one into halves, or such a half.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>반쪽 [반ː쪽]</dt><br>
<dd>1. half</dd><br>
<dd>온전한 하나의 절반.</dd><br>
<dd>A half of the whole.</dd><br>
<dd>2. being sunken</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 평소에 비해 살이 많이 빠져 야윈 모습.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) A state of looking haggard because one has lost a lot of weight.</dd><br>
<dd>3. one's other half</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 연인, 배우자와 같이 매우 가까운 대상.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) A person who is very close to oneself such as a boyfriend, girlfriend, spouse, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>4. imperfection; being incomplete</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 기대에 미치지 못하거나 완벽하지 않은 것.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) A state of not meeting expectations or being imperfect.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>반 [반ː]</dt><br>
<dd>1. half</dd><br>
<dd>둘로 똑같이 나눈 것 가운데 하나.</dd><br>
<dd>One of two things split equally.</dd><br>
<dd>2. half</dd><br>
<dd>일이나 물건의 중간쯤 되는 부분.</dd><br>
<dd>A phrase or part that is in the middle of a certain task or thing.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>verb</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>반분하다 [반ː분하다]</dt><br>
<dd>half; divide in half</dd><br>
<dd>전체를 둘로 똑같이 나누다.</dd><br>
<dd>To divide something up equally in two.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>